text: Fluxinella discula is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Seguenziidae. ==Description== The height of the shell attains 6.5 mm. ==Distribution== This species occurs in the Gulf of Mexico off Texas, in the Caribbean Sea off Cuba and Domenica. ==References== * Rosenberg, G., F. Moretzsohn, and E. F. García. 2009. Gastropoda (Mollusca) of the Gulf of Mexico, Pp. 579–699 in Felder, D.L. and D.K. Camp (eds.), Gulf of Mexico–Origins, Waters, and Biota. Biodiversity. Texas A&M; Press, College Station, Texas. discula Category:Gastropods described in 1889
title: Fluxinella discula
